#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn5:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn5:0.2"
msgid "Anaṅgaṇasutta "
msgstr "Unblemished "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn5:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn5:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn5:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "mn5:1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn5:1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "Sāriputta said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, pts-vp-pli1.25, sc2
msgctxt "mn5:2.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, āvuso, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "mn5:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "mn5:2.3"
msgid "Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "One person with a blemish doesn’t truly understand: ‘There is a blemish in me.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:2.4"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "But another person with a blemish does truly understand: ‘There is a blemish in me.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:2.5"
msgid "Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "One person without a blemish doesn’t truly understand: ‘There is no blemish in me.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:2.6"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "But another person without a blemish does truly understand: ‘There is no blemish in me.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:2.7"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ hīnapuriso akkhāyati. "
msgstr "In this case, of the two persons with a blemish, the one who doesn’t understand is said to be worse, "

msgctxt "mn5:2.8"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyati. "
msgstr "while the one who does understand is better. "

msgctxt "mn5:2.9"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ hīnapuriso akkhāyati. "
msgstr "And of the two persons without a blemish, the one who doesn’t understand is said to be worse, "

msgctxt "mn5:2.10"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "while the one who does understand is better.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn5:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "mn5:3.2"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyati? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, Reverend Sāriputta, what is the reason why, of the two persons with a blemish, one is said to be worse and one better? "

msgctxt "mn5:3.3"
msgid "Ko panāvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyatī”ti? "
msgstr "And what is the cause, what is the reason why, of the two persons without a blemish, one is said to be worse and one better?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc5
msgctxt "mn5:4.1"
msgid "“Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—na chandaṃ janessati na vāyamissati na vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya; "
msgstr "“Reverend, take the case of the person who has a blemish and does not understand it. You can expect that they won’t generate enthusiasm, make an effort, or rouse up energy to give up that blemish. "

msgctxt "mn5:4.2"
msgid "so sarāgo sadoso samoho sāṅgaṇo saṃkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "And they will die with greed, hate, and delusion, blemished, with a corrupted mind. "

msgctxt "mn5:4.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā rajena ca malena ca pariyonaddhā. "
msgstr "Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy covered with dirt or stains. "

#. VAR: pariyodapeyyuṃ → pariyodāpeyyuṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn5:4.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sāmikā na ceva paribhuñjeyyuṃ na ca pariyodapeyyuṃ, rajāpathe ca naṃ nikkhipeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "And the owners neither used it or had it cleaned, but kept it in a dirty place. "

msgctxt "mn5:4.5"
msgid "Evañhi sā, āvuso, kaṃsapāti aparena samayena saṃkiliṭṭhatarā assa malaggahitā”ti? "
msgstr "Over time, wouldn’t that bronze dish get even dirtier and more stained?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:4.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:4.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—na chandaṃ janessati na vāyamissati na vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya; "
msgstr "“In the same way, take the case of the person who has a blemish and does not understand it. You can expect that … "

msgctxt "mn5:4.8"
msgid "so sarāgo sadoso samoho sāṅgaṇo saṃkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "they will die with a corrupted mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli1.26, sc6
msgctxt "mn5:5.1"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—chandaṃ janessati vāyamissati vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya; "
msgstr "Take the case of the person who has a blemish and does understand it. You can expect that they will generate enthusiasm, make an effort, and rouse up energy to give up that blemish. "

msgctxt "mn5:5.2"
msgid "so arāgo adoso amoho anaṅgaṇo asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "And they will die without greed, hate, and delusion, unblemished, with an uncorrupted mind. "

msgctxt "mn5:5.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā rajena ca malena ca pariyonaddhā. "
msgstr "Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy covered with dirt or stains. "

msgctxt "mn5:5.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sāmikā paribhuñjeyyuñceva pariyodapeyyuñca, na ca naṃ rajāpathe nikkhipeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "But the owners used it and had it cleaned, and didn’t keep it in a dirty place. "

msgctxt "mn5:5.5"
msgid "Evañhi sā, āvuso, kaṃsapāti aparena samayena parisuddhatarā assa pariyodātā”ti? "
msgstr "Over time, wouldn’t that bronze dish get cleaner and brighter?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:5.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:5.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—chandaṃ janessati vāyamissati vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya; "
msgstr "“In the same way, take the case of the person who has a blemish and does understand it. You can expect that … "

msgctxt "mn5:5.8"
msgid "so arāgo adoso amoho anaṅgaṇo asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "they will die with an uncorrupted mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc7
msgctxt "mn5:6.1"
msgid "Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—subhanimittaṃ manasi karissati, tassa subhanimittassa manasikārā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃsessati; "
msgstr "Take the case of the person who doesn’t have a blemish but does not understand it. You can expect that they will focus on the feature of beauty, and because of that, lust will infect their mind. "

msgctxt "mn5:6.2"
msgid "so sarāgo sadoso samoho sāṅgaṇo saṅkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "And they will die with greed, hate, and delusion, blemished, with a corrupted mind. "

msgctxt "mn5:6.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā parisuddhā pariyodātā. "
msgstr "Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy clean and bright. "

msgctxt "mn5:6.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sāmikā na ceva paribhuñjeyyuṃ na ca pariyodapeyyuṃ, rajāpathe ca naṃ nikkhipeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "And the owners neither used it or had it cleaned, but kept it in a dirty place. "

