msgid "Evañhi sā, āvuso, kaṃsapāti aparena samayena parisuddhatarā assa pariyodātā”ti? "
msgstr "Over time, wouldn’t that bronze dish get cleaner and brighter?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:7.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:7.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—subhanimittaṃ na manasi karissati, tassa subhanimittassa amanasikārā rāgo cittaṃ nānuddhaṃsessati; "
msgstr "“In the same way, take the case of the person who doesn’t have a blemish and does understand it. You can expect that … "

msgctxt "mn5:7.8"
msgid "so arāgo adoso amoho anaṅgaṇo asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati. "
msgstr "they will die with an uncorrupted mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.27, sc9
msgctxt "mn5:8.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, āvuso moggallāna, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyati. "
msgstr "This is the cause, this is the reason why, of the two persons with a blemish, one is said to be worse and one better. "

msgctxt "mn5:8.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ panāvuso moggallāna, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "And this is the cause, this is the reason why, of the two persons without a blemish, one is said to be worse and one better.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc10
msgctxt "mn5:9.1"
msgid "“Aṅgaṇaṃ aṅgaṇanti, āvuso, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Reverend, the word ‘blemish’ is spoken of. "

msgctxt "mn5:9.2"
msgid "Kissa nu kho etaṃ, āvuso, adhivacanaṃ yadidaṃ aṅgaṇan”ti? "
msgstr "But what is ‘blemish’ a term for?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn5:9.3"
msgid "“Pāpakānaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, akusalānaṃ icchāvacarānaṃ adhivacanaṃ, yadidaṃ aṅgaṇan”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverend, ‘blemish’ is a term for the spheres of bad, unskillful wishes. "

# NOTE: Both MS and BB are unclear as to the speaker here. BB’s section 9 attibutes the proceeding phrases to sariputta. But surely the question is an interjection by Moggallana, as indicated by the punctuation in MS. However, to start a new speaker here, as MS does, is to suggest that this passage is spoken by Moggallana, which is surely incorrect. The close -ti in the previous segment must simply indicated a quoted term.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc11
msgctxt "mn5:10.1"
msgid "“Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish: "

msgctxt "mn5:10.2"
msgid "‘āpattiñca vata āpanno assaṃ, na ca maṃ bhikkhū jāneyyuṃ āpattiṃ āpanno’ti. "
msgstr "‘If I commit an offense, I hope the mendicants don’t find out!’ "

msgctxt "mn5:10.3"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ taṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū jāneyyuṃ: "
msgstr "But it’s possible that the mendicants do find out that that mendicant "

msgctxt "mn5:10.4"
msgid "‘āpattiṃ āpanno’ti. "
msgstr "has committed an offense. "

msgctxt "mn5:10.5"
msgid "‘Jānanti maṃ bhikkhū āpattiṃ āpanno’ti—"
msgstr "Thinking, ‘The mendicants have found out about my offense,’ "

msgctxt "mn5:10.6"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto. "
msgstr "they get angry and bitter. "

msgctxt "mn5:10.7"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr "And that anger and that bitterness "

msgctxt "mn5:10.8"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ. "
msgstr "are both blemishes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc12
msgctxt "mn5:11.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish: "

msgctxt "mn5:11.2"
msgid "‘āpattiñca vata āpanno assaṃ, anuraho maṃ bhikkhū codeyyuṃ, no saṅghamajjhe’ti. "
msgstr "‘If I commit an offense, I hope the mendicants accuse me in private, not in the middle of the Saṅgha.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:11.3"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ taṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū saṅghamajjhe codeyyuṃ, no anuraho. "
msgstr "But it’s possible that the mendicants do accuse that mendicant in the middle of the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "mn5:11.4"
msgid "‘Saṅghamajjhe maṃ bhikkhū codenti, no anuraho’ti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:11.5"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:11.6"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:11.7"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc13
msgctxt "mn5:12.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish: "

msgctxt "mn5:12.2"
msgid "‘āpattiñca vata āpanno assaṃ, sappaṭipuggalo maṃ codeyya, no appaṭipuggalo’ti. "
msgstr "‘If I commit an offense, I hope I’m accused by an equal, not by someone who is not an equal.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:12.3"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ taṃ bhikkhuṃ appaṭipuggalo codeyya, no sappaṭipuggalo. "
msgstr "But it’s possible that someone who is not an equal accuses that mendicant … "

msgctxt "mn5:12.4"
msgid "‘Appaṭipuggalo maṃ codeti, no sappaṭipuggalo’ti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:12.5"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:12.6"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn5:12.7"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, pts-vp-pli1.28, sc14
msgctxt "mn5:13.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish: "

msgctxt "mn5:13.2"
msgid "‘aho vata mameva satthā paṭipucchitvā paṭipucchitvā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseyya, na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ satthā paṭipucchitvā paṭipucchitvā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh, I hope the Teacher will teach the mendicants by repeatedly questioning me alone, not some other mendicant.’ "

msgctxt "mn5:13.3"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ satthā paṭipucchitvā paṭipucchitvā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseyya, na taṃ bhikkhuṃ satthā paṭipucchitvā paṭipucchitvā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseyya. "
